<#
.SYNOPSIS
    This PowerShell script ensures that Windows 10 is configured to audit
    System - Security System Extension successes.
.NOTES
    Author          : Sebastian Chrzanowski
    LinkedIn        : www.linkedin.com/in/sebastian-chrzanowski-75a8a41a4/
    GitHub          : github.com/Viskl
    Date Created    : 2025-03-11
    Last Modified   : 2025-03-11
    Version         : 1.0
    CVEs            : N/A
    Plugin IDs      : N/A
    STIG-ID         : WN10-AU-000150
.TESTED ON
    Date(s) Tested  : 
    Tested By       : 
    Systems Tested  : 
    PowerShell Ver. : 
.USAGE
    Run the script with administrator privileges.
    Example syntax:
    PS C:\> .\remediation_WN10-AU-000150.ps1
#>

# Enable Success auditing for Security System Extension
AuditPol /set /subcategory:"Security System Extension" /success:enable

# Verify the setting was applied
Write-Host "Verification - Current Audit Policy for Security System Extension:"
AuditPol /get /subcategory:"Security System Extension"
